            <p>Artificial Intelligence (AI) is no longer just a buzzword; it’s a reality that’s already making a significant impact across industries. AI is revolutionizing everything from healthcare, where it assists in diagnosing diseases, to finance, where algorithms make trading decisions in milliseconds. In the coming years, AI is expected to become even more integrated into our lives, with advancements in machine learning, natural language processing, and robotics driving innovation. However, as AI becomes more powerful, it also raises ethical questions about privacy, job displacement, and decision-making processes.

